CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1952, pg. 28 reads: "Democratic "Pig Roast" - Democratic workers celebrated at A. Leo Weil School last Thursday night with a mammoth "Pig Roast" and a "Night of Frolic," The Fifth Ward Democratic Committee held the feast and had serving as chefs such well-known personalities as Reese Williamson, James Smith, Joseph Watts, Edward B. Smith, Lonnie Stovall and Curtis Williams, all shown above. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Six chefs including Reese Williamson, James Smith, Joseph Watts, Edward B. Smith, Lonnie Stovall, and Curtis Williams, carving meat for Pig Roast given by the Fifth Ward Democratic Committee at A. Leo Weil School
